From 3925755295cfab2d443258ad03c587c8a3fda63b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "copilot-swe-agent[bot]" <198982749+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 22:34:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: WebGPU browser compatibility

- Add `webgpu` feature to renderer crate
- Add push.rs: PushUniform abstraction for uniform-buffer-based push
  constants on WebGPU targets (var<push_constant> is Vulkan-only)
- Update build.rs to post-process compiled WGSL shaders into
  *_webgpu.wgsl variants replacing var<push_constant> with
  @group(N) @binding(0) var<uniform> when the webgpu feature is active
- Update blit.rs, clear.rs: conditional PushUniform fields and pipeline
  layouts; use push_constant on native, uniform buffer on WebGPU;
  Converter uses separate layouts for color and depth pipelines
- Update lib.rs: add queue to Inner, skip background thread on wasm32,
  store sync_renderer/sync_receiver for synchronous action dispatch
- Update render.rs: pipeline_immediates_uniform field for WebGPU,
  conditional push_constants vs uniform buffer in flush()
- Update render/pipeline.rs: conditional pipeline layout (group 2 for
  push uniform on WebGPU), expose push_uniform_layout()
- Update render/pipeline/shader.rs: replace push_constant declaration
  in render.wesl source when compiling with webgpu feature
- Update render/framebuffer.rs: replace encoder.clear_texture() with
  render pass LoadOp::Clear for WebGPU (CLEAR_TEXTURE is native-only);
  add RENDER_ATTACHMENT usage to external framebuffer on WebGPU;
  pass queue to blit/converter methods
- Gate modules/src/audio.rs behind cfg(not(target_arch = "wasm32"))
- Move cpal/gilrs/resampler/hound to target-specific deps in modules
- Add renderer with webgpu feature to lazuli-web wasm32 dependencies

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>

Co-authored-by: BeezBumba <130922034+BeezBumba@users.noreply.github.com>
